<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>short order • tall order</xh5><p> <i>short order</i>—(U.S.) an order for food to be prepared and served up quickly: A good <u>short-order</u> cook in a well-designed kitchen can plate 100 meals an hour during morning rush.</p><p> <i>tall order—</i>an excessive or unreasonable demand; a difficult task: Miss Maple considered: “It would be better, I think, to find the body first. Don’t you?” “Yes, but isn’t that rather a <u>tall order</u>?”</p> </entry>
